cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection using a deep learning approach, specifically a Fully Convolutional Neural Network (FCN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture and loss function, which involves training the network to learn effective features for detecting salient objects. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a Multi-scale Feature Extraction Module (MFEM) and discusses the importance of contextual information, which could place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on several datasets, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
